mor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-1536x864.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072252/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_angled-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a></p><p>Designed not as a replacement for a suspension fork, but rather for a dedicated rigid adventure bike to keep the front end as low as possible without compromising tire clearance, the non-suspension-corrected Curve GMX+ fork has a short axle-to-crown length of 430mm. (<em>Compare that for example to say to the 411mm a-c Lauf Grit SL with 30mm, or the 506mm a-c RockShox SID SL with 100mm of travel, making the GMX+ shorter than even an 80mm 26″ fork.</em>) With that in mind, there’s still plenty of room for a 29er wheel with a 3″ tire plus some mud, meaning there’s no limit where you can roam.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072245/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_details.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072245/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_details.jpg\" alt=\"Curve GMX+ Carbon monster gravel off-road adventure bikepacking fork for 29x3&quot; tires, details\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072245/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_details.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28072245/Curve-GMX-Carbon-fork_off-road-adventure-bikepacking-fork-with-3-inch-tire-clearance-and-low-axle-crown_details-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-c